.SH "NAME"
pix\-sun \- convert a BRL PIX(5) format image to a Sun Rasterfile format
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBpix\-sun\fP [\-d] [\-s \fIsquaresize\fP] [\-w \fIfile_width\fP] [\-n \fIfile_height\fP] < \fIBRLpixfile\fP > \fIrasterfile\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBpix\-sun\fP converts the \fIBRL PIX(5)\fP format file on the standard
input to a \fISun Rasterfile\fP format file on the standard output.  The
rasterfile produced is a "standard" (as opposed to "byte encoded")
image, with 8 bits per pixel, with a palette of 256 colors.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-d\fP
.RS 4
use a dither map
.RE
.sp
\fB\-n file_height\fP
.RS 4
tells \fBpix\-sun\fP that the input is
\fIfile_height\fP scanlines tall
.RE
.sp
\fB\-s squaresize\fP
.RS 4
sets both the width and the height for the input to
be \fIsquaresize\fP
.RE
.sp
\fB\-w file_width\fP
.RS 4
tells \fBpix\-sun\fP that the input is \fIfile_width\fP
pixels wide
.RE
